         <abstract>
            <p>The lattice structure of points in an n-dimensional space produced by an appropriate grouping of pseudo-random numbers obtained from multiplicative congruential generators is discussed. Examples are given for 2 ≤ n ≤ 6. The work is based on the theory of the reduction of positive quadratic forms in n variables.</p>
          </abstract>
